==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|regretter||to regret}}, variously explained: (a) orig. "bewail" < {{etyl|fro}} {{term|re-}} + *{{term|grater}} from the OLG. form cognate with ..., (b) < {{etyl|la}} {{term|re-}} + {{term|gratus||pleasing}}, as if originally an adjective "unpleasing", (c) < {{ML.}} as if *{{term|regradus||a return (of a disease)}} < {{term|regredi||to go back}}, (d) < {{etyl|la}} as if *{{term|requiritari}} < {{term|re-}} + {{term|quiritare||to bewail}}, (e) < {{etyl|la}} {{term|requiritare||to ask after, inquire for}}.

